Prisoners serving life sentences went on the rampage on Sunday, complaining about the way the parole board operates. JOHANNESBURG - The Department of Correctional Services says the situation is calm at the Kgosi Mampuru prison in Pretoria after a riot in which two people were injured.Prisoners serving life sentences went on the rampage on Sunday, complaining about the way the parole board operates.The department's specialised units were called in to break up the riot.Warders used dogs, electric shields and pepper spray after prisoners attacked them with weapons.The department's Logan Maistry says the situation is under control. Officials managed to bring the situation under control and there have been no reports of further incidents. The department is not aware of any other similar incidents at other correctional facilities in the country. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)